text: Many people grow up with dogs, cats, fish, maybe even a horse, but few have had the pleasure I have of owning a goat. Goats are weird little creatures. They live about the same length as a dog and can learn their name. Also, they get a massive thrill from getting as elevated as they can to overlook everything and will climb on top of rocks, cars, or roofs to make that happen. Once they reach the peak of their surroundings, goats are able to see just about anything they want to due to their 340 degree vision. This comes from their rectangular pupils. Additionally, if there is one thing goats care about it is their brothers. Goats will become depressed if kept without another goat. Finally, many think that Goats will eat anything, and I get it they have four stomachs, they have room to spare. However, they often use their height advantage to reach clean food up in the air. I attached two videos of Indie and OZ as well which were the goats we had. I hope you all have a wonderful day and hopefully I will see you all later.

text:
Hey Taylor,¬†

We at LVIN are aware of the University's confirmed dates for Fall Break Vegas. We were working on switching everyones accounts to the correct date set but then got an error stating the Hotel is short on Double Queen Bed rooms as they oversold the hotel for that weekend due to a huge convention coming into Las Vegas. We know that Single King Bed rooms are not going to work for 4 people, as it will be inconvenient and 4 people cannot share one bed.¬†

We are going to be upgrading everyone to Planet Hollywood Hotel Casino Resort with Double Queen Bed Rooms for the correct date set. Planet Hollywood has a better rating and score with over 10x the amount of reviews¬†than Resorts World. In addition, Planet Hollywood is Center Strip and the location is much better. You will be right across from the Famous Bellagio Fountains, right next door to the Paris Hotel with the Eiffel Tower, and you are connected to the Miracle Mile shops which provides amazing shopping and restaurants. Planet Hollywood also has a very lively casino and is a bit more college friendly than Resorts World, so I'm happy to place ALL of UVA at Planet Hollywood together!

Also, we were able to get 75 more spots for UVA students that still need to sign up! I know a lot of you have been reaching out to get more of your friends signed up, and we are finally able to accommodate them as well! We are also going to extend your $100 off code for another launch week so you can save those friends $100 on the trip cost. I will let you know when the link is live again and ready to go, will definitely be this week!

UVA Confirmed Dates for Vegas Fall Break:
Check-in: September 30th, 2022
Check-out: October 3rd, 2022
